    <example>
      <title>Three Children--Probability of at least 2 girls</title>
      <p>A family has three children. Determine the probability of the family having at least two girls.
        <!--   our own -->
      </p>
      <p>Recall from Example
        <xref ref="example-sample-space-3-children" />the sample space
        <m>SS</m> has
        <m>8</m> outcomes:
        <md>
          <mrow>SS=\{BBB,BBG,BGB,BGG,GBB,GBG,GGB,GGG\}</mrow>
        </md>To determine the probability of the family having at least two girls, first write the event space,
        <m>A</m>
        <md>
          <mrow>A=\{BGG, GBG, GGB, GGG \} \amp\amp\amp \text{The event \(A\) contains \(4\) outcomes with at least \(2\) girls.}</mrow>
          <mrow>P(A) = \dfrac{n(A)}{n(SS)}=\dfrac{4}{8}=\dfrac{1}{2}=0.5\amp\amp\amp \text{Our Solution:}</mrow>
        </md>The probability of the family having at least two girls is
        <m>\dfrac{1}{2}</m> or
        <m>50\%.\checkmark</m>
      </p>
    </example>
